que =C3=97 RPM) =C3=B7 7127</span></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: =
400;">This number 7127 is also not random.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font=
-weight: 400;">We already know, the formula of power is</span></p><p>&nbsp;=
</p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><b>Power (watts) =3D Torque (Nm) =C3=97 (RPM =
=C3=97 2=CF=80 =C3=B7 60)</b></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"=
>At this stage, the result is in watts if torque is in Newton-meters. To co=
nvert into horsepower, we divide by 745.7, because 1 HP =3D 745.7 watts:</s=
pan></p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><b>HP =3D Power(Watts) =C3=B7 745.7</b></l=
i></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">So, the formula of Horsepower i=
f units of torque are in Newton meter becomes</span></p><ul><li aria-level=
=3D"1"><b>HP =3D [Torque =C3=97 RPM =C3=97 2=CF=80 =C3=B7 60] =C3=B7 745.7<=
/b></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Now, similarly, like we d=
id for the previous calculation, we shall input the value of 2=CF=80 =E2=89=
=88 6.2832 into this formula.</span></p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><b>HP =3D =
[Torque =C3=97 RPM =C3=97 6.2832 =C3=B7 60] =C3=B7 745.7</b></li></ul><ul><=
li aria-level=3D"1"><b>HP =3D Torque =C3=97 RPM =C3=97 0.0001403</b></li></=
ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Because multiplying by 0.0001403 is=
 not convenient, we take its reciprocal:</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-w=
eight: 400;">1 =C3=B7 0.0001403 =E2=89=88 7127</span></p><p><span style=3D"=
font-weight: 400;">So we rewrite the equation as:</span></p><ul><li aria-le=
vel=3D"1"><b>HP =3D (Torque =C3=97 RPM) =C3=B7 7127</b></li></ul><ul><li ar=
ia-level=3D"1"><h3>Example Calculation</h3></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font=
-weight: 400;">If an engine produces 300 lb-ft of torque at 4000 RPM, we ca=
n use the formula to find its horsepower. The formula for Horsepower when t=
orque is in lb-ft is:</span></p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><b>HP&nbsp; =3D (T=
orque =C3=97 RPM) =C3=B7 5252</b></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 4=
00;">Substituting the values gives:</span></p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><b>H=
P =3D (300 =C3=97 4000) =C3=B7 5252</b></li></ul><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><=
b>HP =3D 228.6</b></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">So, the en=
gine produces about 229 horsepower at 4000 RPM.</span></p>								</div>
				</div>
