					<h2 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Custom Se=
ttings for Precision Calculations</h2>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-d1deb30 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"d1deb30" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><h3>Supports Metric and Imperial Units</h=
3></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">This horsepower and torque=
 calculator works with both imperial and metric units, which makes it flexi=
ble for different users. You can enter torque in foot-pounds (lb-ft) or in =
Newton-meters (Nm) and get the horsepower result in your chosen format. The=
re is no need to convert units on your own. Once you select the unit for yo=
ur torque input, our horsepower torque calculator applies the correct formu=
la. It uses 5252 when torque is in lb-ft and 7127 when torque is in Nm.</sp=
an></p><ul><li aria-level=3D"1"><h3>Use for Diesel, Gasoline, Electric, or =
Hybrid Systems</h3></li></ul><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The conve=
rsion is based on physics, which means it works the same way for any type o=
f engine or motor. You can use this torque to hp calculator for diesel and =
gasoline engines, electric motors, or hybrid systems. No matter the source,=
 torque at a given speed always translates into horsepower. This makes the =
tool useful across many fields, from automotive to industrial applications.=
 For instance, you can calculate the horsepower of a tractor=E2=80=99s dies=
el engine or an electric motor with the same ease.</span></p>								</div>
